{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-situations-page-tsx","path":"/en/situations/infection-and-general-measures/state-emergency","result":{"data":{"situation":{"title":"State of Emergency","meta_description":"The state of emergency is one of the extraordinary measures of the Constitutional Act on the Security of the Czech Republic. ","content":{"processed":"<h2><strong>State of Emergency </strong></h2>\n<p>The state of emergency is one of the extraordinary measures of the Constitutional Act on the Security of the Czech Republic. <strong>It is announced by the government. </strong></p>\n<p>One of the cases in which the government can declare a state of emergency is in the situation when there is a <strong>dangerous or significant threat to our lives or health.</strong> And this is the current case.</p>\n<p>The government can declare a state of emergency for a <strong>maximum of 30 days.</strong> However, this situation may be <strong>extended with the prior consent of the Chamber of Deputies. </strong></p>\n<p>The state of emergency <strong>ends</strong> with the expiration of the period for which it was declared or with a decision to cancel it. The Government or the Chamber of Deputies can cancel the state of emergency.</p>\n<h2><strong>Crisis measures </strong></h2>\n<p>These are measures <strong>intended to eliminate or ease the consequences of these difficult times.</strong></p>\n<p>The implementation of a crisis measure <strong>can restrict certain rights and freedoms and impose specific obligations.</strong> Crisis measures may be i<strong>ssued by the government in the event of a declared state of emergency</strong> based on the law on Crisis Management and on the Amendment of Certain laws (Crisis Act).</p>\n<p><strong>The effectiveness </strong>of crisis measures was <strong><a href=\"https://www.vlada.cz/assets/media-centrum/aktualne/nouzovy-stav-1373.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external\">prolonged</a> </strong>for the duration of the <strong>state of emergency</strong>.</p>\n"},"path":{"alias":"/situations/infection-and-general-measures/state-emergency"},"changed":"2020-12-24T12:36:42+00:00","valid_from":"2020-11-05T00:00:00+01:00","langcode":"en","created":"2020-11-05T22:17:02+00:00","links":[{"uri":"https://www.zakonyprolidi.cz/cs/1998-110","title":"Constitutional Act on the Security of the Czech Republic (in Czech)"},{"uri":"https://www.zakonyprolidi.cz/cs/2000-240","title":"Crisis Act (in Czech)"}],"relationships":{"region":[{"name":"All regions of Czechia"}],"icon":{"code":"sd_card_alert"},"situation_type":{"name":"Infection and general measures","path":{"alias":"/situations/infection-and-general-measures"},"relationships":{"icon":{"code":"coronavirus"}}},"measures":[],"related_situations":[{"title":"Purpose of the measures","path":{"alias":"/situations/infection-and-general-measures/purpose-measures","langcode":"en"}},{"title":"Measures on free movement","path":{"alias":"/situations/free-movement-people/measures-free-movement","langcode":"en"}},{"title":"What is the purpose of face masks?","path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks/what-purpose-face-masks","langcode":"en"}},{"title":"Penalties","path":{"alias":"/situations/infection-and-general-measures/penalties","langcode":"en"}}]},"questions_answers":[{"question":"Does the state of emergency mean restrictions on free movement?","value":"No. The  state of emergency is a legal framework in which crisis measures are taken. One of the crisis measures is the restriction on the free movement."},{"question":"Is it possible to go to school during the state of emergency?","value":"The state of emergency does not exclude in-person education. However in-person education might be affected by measures taken in the state of emergency"}],"update":null,"valid_to":"2020-12-12T00:00:00+01:00","last_updated":"2020-12-24T00:00:00+01:00"},"situationArea":{"name":"Infection and general measures","path":{"alias":"/situations/infection-and-general-measures"},"relationsh